3. cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper uses mathematical tools such as the Kalman filter and information theory concepts to analyze the observability of the system. 
4. cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science): The paper involves extensive simulations to validate the theoretical results, which falls under the scope of computational engineering. 
5. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper discusses the design of an optimal tumbling strategy and state observer, which can be seen as an application of AI techniques.
